<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/52416699-jodie">jodie </a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">The religious figures talked about in this book other than those that you have already mentioned are Jonah, Ezekiel, Daniel, and Moses. Jonah is talke<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">The religious figures talked about in this book other than those that you have already mentioned are Jonah, Ezekiel, Daniel, and Moses. Jonah is talked about twice (I think?) towards the end, and Moses once. A Leviathan is also mentioned during the lake scene, however I don't know if that has any symbolism towards the novel as a whole. There is a lot of talk about the lion's den which connects to Daniel, as I think that's mentioned in the novel around 2-3 times?<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
