  <span id="freeText13172507512171447673" style="display:none">I have now read both novels and many of O'Connor's short stories, and my first observation is that she is a brilliant author, but difficult and not very pleasant to read. Her characters are all haunted, and in both this and Wise Blood, insanity rules. Dark and depressing. I prefer her short stories. No star rating because I have no idea. I may return to rate it later, as I mull it over.</span>
