<span id="freeTextContainer7792971492075600624">Everyone should read Flannery O&apos;Connor, but I wouldn&apos;t start with this novel. First read some short stories--my favorite is Good Country People. But this novel is well written and very her. I love her bizzareness and the Southernness that just pervades everything she writes. Her characters are so amazingly real and yet completely unreal at the same time. She makes the unbelievable believable without seeming to try.</span>
