    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_3534786633" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3534786633" />
    <a title="Bob" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/4814165-bob"><img alt="Bob" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1295123458p2/4814165.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3534786633?book_show_action=true">Sep 11, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Bob" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Bob" href="/user/show/4814165-bob">Bob</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/52064199-the-violent-bear-it-away">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/4814165-bob?shelf=fiction-general">fiction-general</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/4814165-bob?shelf=20th-century-classics">20th-century-classics</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3534786633" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15735044325765654300">3.5 Stars rounded up<br/><br/>Up until now my adventures with Flannery O’Connor has been limited to a handful of short stories. The most memorable of these is Revelation, which I first read about 40 years ago. It was a story that stuck with me. Sadly I forgot or never knew who authored it. Because of the southern nature of the writing I always attributed it to being authored by Faulkner. A few years ago I was surprised, when I read a story titled Revelation by Flannery O’Conner and it was the same story I</span>
  <span id="freeText15735044325765654300" style="display:none">3.5 Stars rounded up<br /><br />Up until now my adventures with Flannery O’Connor has been limited to a handful of short stories. The most memorable of these is Revelation, which I first read about 40 years ago. It was a story that stuck with me. Sadly I forgot or never knew who authored it. Because of the southern nature of the writing I always attributed it to being authored by Faulkner. A few years ago I was surprised, when I read a story titled Revelation by Flannery O’Conner and it was the same story I had read so many years ago. Until this discovery I had only heard of Flannery O’Conner. Correcting this mistake started me on the hunt to find and read more written by her. When I came across her story A Good Man Is Hard to Find, I should have known then just how dark O’Conner could write. <br /><br />Being forewarned, I should not have been so surprised at how troubling a read The Violent Bear it Away, turned out to be. So, how does one write a review of a brilliantly written book, when you dislike almost everything about the story? <br /><br />Objectively, I don’t think I can, so don’t take my words to critically. Mostly, I disliked the characters. <a class="jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction">(view spoiler)</a><span class="spoilerContainer" style="display: none">[Old man Tarwater, was a mean spirited cantankerous religious zealot. Who believing he was a prophet of God and right in all things, acted as he saw fit. Never thinking or caring about consequences to him or others. George Raybear, the school teacher, to me was as bad in his anti-religious zeal as the old man was dogmatic toward his idea of religion. Young Tarwater, was simply insane. He was probably driven that way being raised by the evil old man. <a class="jsHideSpoiler spoilerAction">(hide spoiler)</a>]</span> <br /> <br />How can I almost hate this story and still think the book is worthy of merit. Simple, the writing is good. The story is well plotted and the reading flows smoothly. But most important, the author succeeded in planting this story in my mind and I will remember it for years, even though it is a weed.<br /><br />“He kept on digging but the grave did not get any deeper. “The dead are poor,” he said in the voice of the stranger. You can’t be any poorer than dead.”<br />― Flannery O'Connor, The Violent Bear it Away<br /><br /> “The world was made for the dead. Think of all the dead there are...There's a million times more dead than living and the dead are dead a million times longer than the living are alive...”<br />― Flannery O'Connor, The Violent Bear It Away<br /><br />**On a side note, I have a cousin that reminds me of young Tarwater. He too will let any thought that enters his brain jump straight out of his mouth. No thought about right or wrong, true of false, and completely uncaring if another’s feelings are hurt with his words. Couldn’t help but think about him while read this.</span>
  <a data-text-id="15735044325765654300" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

<tr class="no_border feedFooterReview" id="update_comment_stuff_Review3534786633">
  <td colspan="2">
    <div class="updateActionLinks">
        <a class="right flag" rel="nofollow" id="flag_link3534786633" title="Flag this review as inappropriate." href="/flagged/new?resource_id=3534786633&amp;resource_type=Review&amp;return_url=%2Fbook%2Fshow%2F534489.The_Violent_Bear_It_Away">flag</a>





      <span class='likeItContainer' id='like_container_review_3534786633'><a id="like_count_review_3534786633" rel="nofollow" href="/rating/voters/3534786633?resource_type=Review"><span class="likesCount">15 likes</span></a>&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;<a rel="nofollow" class="jsLike like_it gr-button gr-button--small" href="https://www.goodreads.com/user/new?remember=true&amp;return_url=%2Fbook%2Fshow%2F534489.The_Violent_Bear_It_Away">Like</a></span>
&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;<a href="/review/show/3534786633?book_show_action=true&amp;from_review_page=1">see review</a>
    </div>


    <div id='comments_for_review_3534786633' style='display: none;'>
