<div id="review_2367465377" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2367465377" />
    <a title="Kathleen" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/48502194-kathleen"><img alt="Kathleen" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1447215825p2/48502194.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2367465377?book_show_action=true">Apr 28, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Kathleen" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Kathleen" href="/user/show/48502194-kathleen">Kathleen</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780374505240" href="/book/show/48468.The_Violent_Bear_It_Away">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/48502194-kathleen?shelf=women-writers">women-writers</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/48502194-kathleen?shelf=2018-challenges">2018-challenges</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/48502194-kathleen?shelf=2018-reading-women-challenge">2018-reading-women-challenge</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2367465377" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer9361181141047274046">There’s a difference between dark and dreary. Dreary is when you take dark out and expose it to the light until its mysteriousness is gone and you see how sad it is. This story is dreary.<br/><br/>But the writing is breathtaking, arresting. I won’t soon forget these characters. Flannery O’Connor is astounding in the way she explores forbidden territory. She takes her stories to what you think is the edge, and then she goes a step further.<br/><br/>This one is about 14 year-old Francis Marion Tarwater and his fate. </span>
  <span id="freeText9361181141047274046" style="display:none">There’s a difference between dark and dreary. Dreary is when you take dark out and expose it to the light until its mysteriousness is gone and you see how sad it is. This story is dreary.<br /><br />But the writing is breathtaking, arresting. I won’t soon forget these characters. Flannery O’Connor is astounding in the way she explores forbidden territory. She takes her stories to what you think is the edge, and then she goes a step further.<br /><br />This one is about 14 year-old Francis Marion Tarwater and his fate. There is a literal wrestling of that fate played out: between him and his great uncle, him and his uncle, him and his self, him and the outside world. <br /><br /><i>“The boy thrust his head forward. ‘I’m free,’ he hissed. ‘I’m outside your head. I ain’t in it. I ain’t in it and I ain’t about to be.’”</i><br /><br />Are any of us really free that way? It was particularly disturbing to read this now, given the current political climate. Education was meant to give us opportunity to look at the facts and understand things for ourselves. But now we can’t even agree on what the facts are. We should be able to determine our own destiny to a certain extent, but there are still so many with a control over us, a control that appears to be more powerful than reason. This story explores that kind of control, and I found it troubling indeed.</span>
  <a data-text-id="9361181141047274046" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


