    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_2991401887" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2991401887" />
    <a title="Jesse" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/1432036-jesse"><img alt="Jesse" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1612374946p2/1432036.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2991401887?book_show_action=true">Sep 26, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Jesse" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Jesse" href="/user/show/1432036-jesse">Jesse</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780374505240" href="/book/show/48468.The_Violent_Bear_It_Away">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1432036-jesse?shelf=american-lit">american-lit</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1432036-jesse?shelf=women-writers">women-writers</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1432036-jesse?shelf=religion-and-mysticism">religion-and-mysticism</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1432036-jesse?shelf=read-in-2019">read-in-2019</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1432036-jesse?shelf=haunting-and-spectrality">haunting-and-spectrality</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1432036-jesse?shelf=1960-s">1960-s</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2991401887" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12942338116823652199">Second reading. A dark, inevitably violent novel; the physical violence is occasional, but the spiritual antagonism is incessant and oppressive. The undeniably gorgeous writing animates a deeply apocalyptic vision: O&apos;Connor presents a fallen world where the devil walks among humanity and prophecy is the genuine calling of the elect. It brought back powerful memories of reading the Old Testament as a child and taking its stories as historical fact deeply applicable to my own life, the incontrover</span>
  <span id="freeText12942338116823652199" style="display:none">Second reading. A dark, inevitably violent novel; the physical violence is occasional, but the spiritual antagonism is incessant and oppressive. The undeniably gorgeous writing animates a deeply apocalyptic vision: O'Connor presents a fallen world where the devil walks among humanity and prophecy is the genuine calling of the elect. It brought back powerful memories of reading the Old Testament as a child and taking its stories as historical fact deeply applicable to my own life, the incontrovertible proof that my unremarkable everyday reality was a mere curtain separating me from an ancient high-stakes battle waged across both the earthly and spiritual realms. <br /><br />I don't at all miss inhabiting this world but find it helpful to revisit such terrain on occasion. I couldn't help but feel on this rereading it captures an aspect of the American psyche that feels eerily familiar again, having reemerged with overwhelming dominance in our current historical moment.<br /><br /><i>"The sky was a bright pink, casting such a weird light that every color was intensified. Each weed that grew out of the gravel looked like a live green nerve. The world might have been shedding its own skin."</i></span>
  <a data-text-id="12942338116823652199" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


